<content>
<para id="fs-id1903490">The digestive system uses mechanical and chemical activities to break food down into absorbable substances during its journey through the digestive system. <link target-id="tbl-ch24_03" document=""/> provides an overview of the basic functions of the digestive organs.</para>
<note id="fs-id793571" class="anatomy interactive">
<label/>
<para id="fs-id2267916">Visit this <link url="http://openstax.org/l/fooddigestion2">site</link> for an overview of digestion of food in different regions of the digestive tract. Note the route of non-fat nutrients from the small intestine to their release as nutrients to the body.</para>
</note>
