<section id="fs-id1984735" class="free-response">
<title>Critical Thinking Questions</title>
<exercise id="fs-id841238">
<problem id="fs-id1363988"><para id="fs-id2311288">Offer a theory to explain why segmentation occurs and peristalsis slows in the small intestine.</para></problem>
<solution id="fs-id1866459"><label/>
<para id="fs-id969728">The majority of digestion and absorption occurs in the small intestine. By slowing the transit of chyme, segmentation and a reduced rate of peristalsis allow time for these processes to occur.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id1237051">
<problem id="fs-id2239397"><para id="fs-id1879791">It has been several hours since you last ate. Walking past a bakery, you catch a whiff of freshly baked bread. What type of reflex is triggered, and what is the result?</para></problem>
<solution id="fs-id1493241"><label/>
<para id="fs-id1413106">The smell of food initiates long reflexes, which result in the secretion of digestive juices.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
